node.text: We made these simple fishcakes last night using the leftover mashed potatoes and some home smoked Trout which we had in the freezer.  Flake the mash and stir in the flaked smoked trout, add some horseradish sauce, some capers, some Thai green curry paste, a little ketchup manis or sweet chilli sauce,  I also threw in the leftover bread sauce.  Season.. Mix it together,  if you like them quite spicy then add a little lazy red chilli. Roll in to patties and toss in some breadcrumbs mixed with Panko then fry gently and pop in the oven until you are ready to eat them.  #fishcakes #leftovers #eatingupthefridge #simplesuppers #deliciousquicksuppers #mashedpotatoes #smokedtrout #easyrecipes #healthynutritiousfood #eatfresh #cookeasily #foodinlockdown #covidcooking #covidcookery #stircrazy

node.text:
Posted @withregram ‚Ä¢ @overripe_ I've always been super curious about anything to do with eating and drinking. This inquisitiveness made me try kombucha for the first time 2 years ago. It is an ancient fermented tea that is high on probiotics and low on calories. The slightly tarty taste along with its multiple health benefits had me hooked! Sadly, most of the brands available in the Indian market make use of artificial carbonation and filtration while adding too much sugar for the beverage to be considered even remotely healthy. 

The COVID lockdown presented me with the perfect chance to start brewing my own kombucha at home and get experimental. Soon, I was sending out bottles to close friends and after weeks of iterations and product development urged by friends and family, I felt confident enough to present my yummy, naturally fizzy and healthy kombucha to a broader audience as @sach.booch. Our potent combination of tea, probiotics and whole fruits & herbs boosts digestion and immunity while reducing bloating. 

Being a craft kombucha brewery, everything is self-funded and handmade, right down to the labels. We have a greater ability to be innovative with our ingredients and ensure top-notch quality for each bottle. There is no added sugar in our kombucha, no artificial carbonation, only whole fruits and herbs with the best blend of organic teas. 

The journey has been akin to a roller-coaster with every new order and positive customer feedback being the exhilarating highs; and minimal IG engagement and failed experiments bringing in the lows. We're constantly learning from this experience and getting better, expanding our reach. What we will never lose sight of is the reason why we started: ensuring we provide a wholesome and genuine dose of probiotics which happens to be so tasty that you forget its healthy.

Story by @reshizzle 
Illustration by @artbychibs @shivangiikhanna

node.text:
Posted @withregram ‚Ä¢ @overripe_ It was really great to be able to replicate the iconic New Yorkers in town and bring it to the suburbs. As restaurateurs, the natural next step was for us to pivot into catering. We had been catering for more than 12 years when Covid-19 happened and the lockdown was imposed. Like many others in the hospitality industry, our business took a major hit during this time.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Just when we were at the point of no return, people started getting acclimatized to the new quarantined way of life. Soon enough a bunch of our regular clients started calling us and enquiring whether we could deliver our food to them. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
The key to a successful business is adapting to change and staying alert to opportunities of growth. Our opportunity had arrived. We promptly started working on a specialized menu for our clients and the response was remarkable! ‚†Ä
Word of mouth led to our menu being passed around and we started getting more orders than we had anticipated or ever received before.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
We offer quite a selection of fares but our two most popular dishes are the Marine Drive Meal and the Mediterranean Meal. We receive more orders for these two specials than for any other item on our set menu. The overwhelming feedback has only boosted our plans and we have now decided to go all out and start catering our meals to the entire city!‚†Ä
‚†Ä
We want to start an all-inclusive delivery service across Mumbai right from the heart of our operation ‚Äì our centralized home kitchen.‚†Ä
Our motto is simple and we stuck to it during the lockdown - Good Food for Everyone. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Story by @aryanshah277 @masalakraftkitchen 
Illustration by @artbychibs @shivangiikhanna ‚†Ä

I've always been super curious about anything to do with eating and drinking. This inquisitiveness made me try kombucha for the first time 2 years ago. It is an ancient fermented tea that is high on probiotics and low on calories. The slightly tarty taste along with its multiple health benefits had me hooked! Sadly, most of the brands available in the Indian market make use of artificial carbonation and filtration while adding too much sugar for the beverage to be considered even remotely healthy. 

The COVID lockdown presented me with the perfect chance to start brewing my own kombucha at home and get experimental. Soon, I was sending out bottles to close friends and after weeks of iterations and product development urged by friends and family, I felt confident enough to present my yummy, naturally fizzy and healthy kombucha to a broader audience as @sach.booch. Our potent combination of tea, probiotics and whole fruits & herbs boosts digestion and immunity while reducing bloating. 

Being a craft kombucha brewery, everything is self-funded and handmade, right down to the labels. We have a greater ability to be innovative with our ingredients and ensure top-notch quality for each bottle. There is no added sugar in our kombucha, no artificial carbonation, only whole fruits and herbs with the best blend of organic teas. 

The journey has been akin to a roller-coaster with every new order and positive customer feedback being the exhilarating highs; and minimal IG engagement and failed experiments bringing in the lows. We're constantly learning from this experience and getting better, expanding our reach. What we will never lose sight of is the reason why we started: ensuring we provide a wholesome and genuine dose of probiotics which happens to be so tasty that you forget its healthy.

Story by @reshizzle 
Illustration by @artbychibs @shivangiikhanna

node.text:
It‚Äôs been weeks since we picked the last of the apples in our garden weeks ago, and we‚Äôre still looking for ways to use up the more battered ones. Someone suggested tarte tatin, a kind of upside-down apple pie, which I‚Äôve eaten in restaurants and, very memorably, in the cosy kitchen of my culinary friend M‚Äôs thatched cottage in Hampshire, years ago. I‚Äôve always thought it would be just too complicated for me to make myself ~ M is a much better cook than I am ~ and I also had my doubts about putting a frying pan in the oven. But guess what? If you use ready-made puff pastry it‚Äôs easy as, well, pie. And our frying pan has lived to tell the tale.

Tarte tatin 

50g butter
50g caster sugar
one vanilla pod, and seeds
three apples, peeled, cored and cut into quarters
one pack ready rolled puff pastry
one egg, beaten

Preheat your oven to 200C.

Melt the butter and the sugar together in a 20cm frying pan. Arrange the apples snugly in a wheel ~ they will shrink as they cook, so don‚Äôt worry if there seem to be too many ~ and cook them for 8 to 10 minutes, until they‚Äôre soft. Take the pan off heat and let it cool for a few minutes.

Unroll the puff pastry and cut out a circle a little larger than the diameter of the frying pan. Lay it over the apples, tucking it in at the edges so you can‚Äôt see any of the fruit. Prick the pastry all over with a fork, then bake in the oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until the pasty is golden brown and risen.

Take the tart out of the oven and leave it to cool for five minutes. Run a small knife between the pastry and the pan. Put a serving plate, upside down, on top of the pan, then turn the whole thing over and remove the frying pan, so that you‚Äôre left with a delicious layer of caramelised apples on top of the pastry.

We like this best served with creÃÄme fraiÃÇche, but it‚Äôs also good with vanilla ice cream.

It was really great to be able to replicate one of the iconic in town and bring it to the suburbs. As restaurateurs, the natural next step was for us to pivot into catering. We had been catering for more than 12 years when Covid-19 happened and the lockdown was imposed. Like many others in the hospitality industry, our business took a major hit during this time.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Just when we were at the point of no return, people started getting acclimatized to the new quarantined way of life. Soon enough a bunch of our regular clients started calling us and enquiring whether we could deliver our food to them. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
The key to a successful business is adapting to change and staying alert to opportunities of growth. Our opportunity had arrived. We promptly started working on a specialized menu for our clients and the response was remarkable! ‚†Ä
Word of mouth led to our menu being passed around and we started getting more orders than we had anticipated or ever received before.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
We offer quite a selection of fares but our two most popular dishes are the Marine Drive Meal and the Mediterranean Meal. We receive more orders for these two specials than for any other item on our set menu. The overwhelming feedback has only boosted our plans and we have now decided to go all out and start catering our meals to the entire city!‚†Ä
‚†Ä
We want to start an all-inclusive delivery service across Mumbai right from the heart of our operation ‚Äì our centralized home kitchen.‚†Ä
Our motto is simple and we stuck to it during the lockdown - Good Food for Everyone. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Story by @aryanshah277 @masalakraftkitchen

node.text:
Posted @withregram ‚Ä¢ @overripe_ It all began with the lockdown...

Being an Oral and Maxillofacial surgeon meant that most of my time was spent among course books and I never really got any time to enter the kitchen even though I liked cooking. However, with all the house help having returned home to their villages during the lockdown, the chores had to be divided among mom, dad and me. That‚Äôs when I voluntarily declared, ‚ÄúI‚Äôll do the cooking!‚Äù

At that point the only thought in my head was that it was a good opportunity to learn some basic cooking skills so that I could at least manage my own hunger in times of need. 

As the days progressed and I started cooking religiously, my cravings for delectable, restaurant-style food amplified. That‚Äôs when I developed an interest in cooking, recipes and trying my hand at cooking different cuisines. What‚Äôs more, the dishes turned out to be astonishingly good and I was showered with praises from my parents. 

When the lockdown eased after a few months, I started visiting my maternal grandmother‚Äôs home and on each visit I made sure to bring along some of my handmade dishes for everyone at home to try. My mama and mami really loved the food and in fact it was my mami who came up with the idea for me to open up a home kitchen. Without overthinking it, we created an Instagram account called @delicravings_rhea and just waited to see what would happen. With God‚Äôs grace, I started receiving orders the very next day and I haven‚Äôt looked back since.
 
Now even though work has resumed as per usual and the schedules are getting hectic again, I take orders and fulfill them with the same care, precaution and lots and lots of love. 

The one thing I‚Äôve realized is that no matter how busy our lives may seem, we must always make time for our passions. I hope to always continue cooking, baking and feeding people delicious home cooked meals

Story by @dr.rhee_k 
Illustration by @artbychibs @shivangiikhanna
